{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_64","type":"agent_message","text":"The multipart failure is now pinned down: WireMock reflectively calls `org.apache.commons.fileupload.MultipartStream.newInputStream()`, and native-image doesn’t have that method registered, so Jetty returns `500`. I’m adding that reflection entry to the WireMock metadata and extending the temporary HTTPS diagnostics to print the error body too, because that path is also returning `500` rather than throwing the expected socket-close `IOException`."}}
