{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_112","type":"agent_message","text":"The decompiled fault injector exposed a likely missing-reflection path: `Jetty11HttpUtils.tlsSocket(...)` reflectively calls `endPoint.getClass().getMethod(\"getChannel\").invoke(...)` to get the underlying TLS socket. If that reflective `getChannel` isn’t registered, WireMock would throw inside the fault handler and convert the fault into a plain `500`, which matches what we’re seeing."}}
